A: The problem is that you're not actually getting the value of the checkboxes. You're comparing the fieldname with "Mcheckbox" and "Echeckbox", but you're not storing the value in fieldvalue.
You should use fi.getString() to get the value of the checkboxes.
Here's how you can modify your code:
while (it.hasNext()) {
    FileItem fi = (FileItem) it.next();
    if (fi.isFormField()) {
        if (fi.getFieldName().compareTo("Mcheckbox") == 0) {
            System.out.println("checkbox value is " + fi.getString());
            mymobilepass = fi.getString();
        } else if (fi.getFieldName().compareTo("Echeckbox") == 0) {
            System.out.println("checkbox value is " + fi.getString());
            myemailpass = fi.getString();
        }
    } else {
        // your code to handle the file upload
    }
}

This will correctly get the value of the checkboxes and store it in mymobilepass and myemailpass.
Also, make sure that your checkboxes are correctly named "Mcheckbox" and "Echeckbox" in your HTML form.

